Package: revana
Title: Regulatory Variant Analysis and Visualization of Cancer Genomes
Version: 0.9.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Elias",
           family = "Ulrich",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "elias.ulrich@kitz-heidelberg.de",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2489-7265"))
Description: Revana is a comprehensive tool for regulatory variant detection. It can detect, analyse, and illustrate regulatory variants of different kinds. It works on whole genome (WGS) and RNA sequencing (RNA-Seq) data of a cohort of tumor samples and creates interactive HTML reports summarizing the most important regulatory events.
